      "text": [
        "مَنْ عَقَدَ اَلْإِحْرَامَ فِي مَسْجِدِ اَلشَّجَرَةِ ثُمَّ وَقَعَ عَلَى أَهْلِهِ قَبْلَ أَنْ يُلَبِّيَ قَالَ «لَيْسَ عَلَيْهِ شَيْءٌ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2565 - Hafs ibn al-Bakhtari narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding someone who entered Ihram at Masjid al-Shajarah and then had intercourse with his spouse before reciting the Talbiyah.\nImam (as) said: \"There is nothing upon him [no penalty].\""
        ]
      }
    },
